# Chromium Lambda Layer

This directory is used by CDK to create a Lambda Layer containing:
- @sparticuz/chromium (Chromium binary for Lambda)
- playwright-core (Playwright browser automation)

The layer is automatically built during CDK deployment using Docker bundling.

## How it works

1. CDK uses the bundling configuration in minimal-stack.ts
2. Docker container installs the required npm packages
3. Packages are placed in /nodejs directory (Lambda layer convention)
4. Layer is uploaded to AWS Lambda
5. Lambda functions reference the layer for browser automation

## Manual testing (optional)

To test the layer locally:

```bash
cd packages/backend/layers/chromium
mkdir -p nodejs
cd nodejs
npm init -y
npm install @sparticuz/chromium playwright-core
```

This creates a local version of what CDK will build automatically.
